  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This Emergency Appeal seeks a total of 7,7 million Swiss francs to enable the International Federation of Red Cross and Red Crescent Societies (IFRC) to support four National Societies in Southern Africa (Botswana, Eswatini, Lesotho and Namibia) to deliver assistance to 81,000 people (16,200 households) affected by a worsening drought for 14 months with a focus on Livelihoods and Basic Needs. The planned response reflects the current situation and information available at this time of the operation.</narrative>
